column9: Or sugchuno (soong-khoo'-no) from  (G4862) sun and cheo (to pour) or its alternate; to commingle promiscuously, i.e. (figuratively) to throw (an assembly) into disorder, to perplex (the mind) -- confound, confuse, stir up, be in an uproar. see GREEK  (G4862) sun

column7: to use together with, to associate with
column9: From  (G4862) sun and  (G5530) chraomai; to use jointly, i.e. (by implication) to hold intercourse in common -- have dealings with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G5530) chraomai
From  (G4797) sugcheo; commixture, i.e. (figuratively) riotous disturbance -- confusion. see GREEK  (G4797) sugcheo
From  (G4862) sun and  (G2198) zao; to continue to live in common with, i.e. Co-survive (literally or figuratively) -- live with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G2198) zao
From  (G4862) sun and the base of  (G2201) zeugos; to yoke together, i.e. (figuratively) conjoin (in marriage) -- join together. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G2201) zeugos

From  (G4862) sun and  (G2212) zeteo; to investigate jointly, i.e. Discuss, controvert, cavil -- dispute (with), enquire, question (with), reason (together). see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G2212) zeteo
From  (G4802) suzeteo; mutual questioning, i.e. Discussion -- disputation(-ting), reasoning. see GREEK  (G4802) suzeteo
From  (G4802) suzeteo; a disputant, i.e. Sophist -- disputer. see GREEK  (G4802) suzeteo
From  (G4801) suzeugnumi; co-yoked, i.e. (figuratively) as noun, a colleague; probably rather as a proper name; Syzygus, a Christian -- yokefellow. see GREEK  (G4801) suzeugnumi
From  (G4862) sun and  (G2227) zoopoieo; to reanimate conjointly with (figuratively) -- quicken together with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G2227) zoopoieo
Of Hebrew origin ( (H8256) shaqam) in imitation of  (G4809) sukomoraia; a sycamore-fig tree -- sycamine tree. see GREEK  (G4809) sukomoraia see HEBREW  (H8256) shaqam
From  (G4810) sukon; a fig-tree -- fig tree. see GREEK  (G4810) sukon
From  (G4810) sukon and moron (the mulberry); the "sycamore"-fig tree -- sycamore tree. Compare  (G4807) sukaminos. see GREEK  (G4810) sukon see GREEK  (G4807) sukaminos
Apparently a primary word; a fig -- fig.

column8: accuse falsely, take by false accusation.
column9: From a compound of  (G4810) sukon and a derivative of  (G5316) phaino; to be a fig-informer (reporter of the law forbidding the exportation of figs from Greece), "sycophant", i.e. (genitive and by extension) to defraud (exact unlawfully, extort) -- accuse falsely, take by false accusation. see GREEK  (G4810) sukon see GREEK  (G5316) phaino
From the base of  (G4813) sulao and (the reduplicated form of)  (G71) ago; to lead away as booty, i.e. (figuratively) seduce -- spoil. see GREEK  (G4813) sulao see GREEK  (G71) ago
From a derivative of sullo (to strip; probably akin to  (G138) haireomai; compare  (G4661) skulon); to despoil -- rob. see GREEK  (G138) haireomai see GREEK  (G4661) skulon
From  (G4862) sun and  (G2980) laleo; to talk together, i.e. Converse -- commune (confer, talk) with, speak among. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G2980) laleo

column7: to collect, to take, by implication to take part with, to conceive
column9: From  (G4862) sun and  (G2983) lambano; to clasp, i.e. Seize (arrest, capture); specially, to conceive (literally or figuratively); by implication, to aid -- catch, conceive, help, take. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G2983) lambano
From  (G4862) sun and  (G3004) lego in its original sense; to collect -- gather (together, up). see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G3004) lego

column7: to reckon, to compute, to reason
column9: From  (G4862) sun and  (G3049) logizomai; to reckon together (with oneself), i.e. Deliberate -- reason with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G3049) logizomai

column7: to be moved to grief with (pass.)
column9: From  (G4862) sun and  (G3076) lupeo; to afflict jointly, i.e. (passive) sorrow at (on account of) someone -- be grieved. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G3076) lupeo

column7: to come together, (of events) to come to pass
column9: From  (G4862) sun and the base of  (G939) basis; to walk (figuratively, transpire) together, i.e. Concur (take place) -- be(-fall), happen (unto). see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G939) basis

column7: to throw together, to discuss, consider, meet with
column9: From  (G4862) sun and  (G906) ballo; to combine, i.e. (in speaking) to converse, consult, dispute, (mentally) to consider, (by implication) to aid, (personally) to join, attack -- confer, encounter, help, make, meet with, ponder. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G906) ballo
From  (G4862) sun and  (G936) basileuo; to be co-regent (figuratively) -- reign with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G936) basileuo

column7: to join together, to consider,  to teach
column9: From  (G4862) sun and bibazo (to force; causative (by reduplication) of the base of  (G939) basis); to drive together, i.e. Unite (in association or affection), (mentally) to infer, show, teach -- compact, assuredly gather, intrust, knit together, prove. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G939) basis

From  (G4862) sun and  (G1011) bouleuo; to give (or take) advice jointly, i.e. Recommend, deliberate or determine -- consult, (give, take) counsel (together). see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G1011) bouleuo

Neuter of a presumed derivative of  (G4825) sumboulos; advisement; specially, a deliberative body, i.e. The provincial assessors or lay-court -- consultation, counsel, council. see GREEK  (G4825) sumboulos
From  (G4862) sun and  (G1012) boule; a consultor, i.e. Adviser -- counsellor. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G1012) boule

column7: Symeon, Simeon, the name of several Israelites, also a tribe of Isr
column9: From the same as  (G4613) Simon; Symeon (i.e. Shimon), the name of five Israelites -- Simeon, Simon. see GREEK  (G4613) Simon
From a compound of  (G4862) sun and  (G3129) manthano; a co-learner (of Christianity) -- fellow disciple. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G3129) manthano

column7: to testify or bear witness with
column9: From  (G4862) sun and  (G3140) martureo; to testify jointly, i.e. Corroborate by (concurrent) evidence -- testify unto, (also) bear witness (with). see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G3140) martureo
Middle voice from  (G4862) sun and  (G3307) merizo; to share jointly, i.e. Participate in -- be partaker with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G3307) merizo

column7: partaking with, subst. a joint partaker
column9: From  (G4862) sun and  (G3353) metochos; a co-participant -- partaker. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G3353) metochos
From a presumed compound of  (G4862) sun and  (G3401) mimeomai; a co-imitator, i.e. Fellow votary -- follower together. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G3401) mimeomai
From  (G4862) sun and  (G3444) morphe; jointly formed, i.e. (figuratively) similar -- conformed to, fashioned like unto. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G3444) morphe

column7: conform to, fashion self according to
column8: conform to, fashion self according to.
column9: From  (G4832) summorphos; to render like, i.e. (figuratively) to assimilate -- make conformable unto. see GREEK  (G4832) summorphos

column7: to have a fellow feeling with, sympathize with
column9: From  (G4835) sumpathes; to feel "sympathy" with, i.e. (by implication) to commiserate -- have compassion, be touched with a feeling of. see GREEK  (G4835) sumpathes
From  (G4841) sumpascho; having a fellow-feeling ("sympathetic"), i.e. (by implication) mutually commiserative -- having compassion one of another. see GREEK  (G4841) sumpascho

From  (G4862) sun and  (G3854) paraginomai; to be present together, i.e. To convene; by implication, to appear in aid -- come together, stand with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G3854) paraginomai

column7: to exhort together, pass. to be strengthened with
column9: From  (G4862) sun and  (G3870) parakaleo; to console jointly -- comfort together. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G3870) parakaleo
From  (G4862) sun and  (G3880) paralambano; to take along in company -- take with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G3880) paralambano
From  (G4862) sun and  (G3887) parameno; to remain in company, i.e. Still live -- continue with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G3887) parameno
From  (G4862) sun and  (G3918) pareimi; to be at hand together, i.e. Now present -- be here present with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G3918) pareimi

From  (G4862) sun and  (G3958) pascho (including its alternate); to experience pain jointly or of the same kind (specially, persecution; to "sympathize") -- suffer with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G3958) pascho
From  (G4862) sun and  (G3992) pempo; to despatch in company -- send with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G3992) pempo

From  (G4862) sun and a compound of  (G4012) peri and  (G2983) lambano; to take by enclosing altogether, i.e. Earnestly throw the arms about one -- embrace. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G4012) peri see GREEK  (G2983) lambano
From  (G4862) sun and  (G4095) pino; to partake a beverage in company -- drink with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G4095) pino

column7: to fill up completely, to fulfill
column9: From  (G4862) sun and  (G4137) pleroo; to implenish completely, i.e. (of space) to swamp (a boat), or (of time) to accomplish (passive, be complete) -- (fully) come, fill up. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G4137) pleroo
From  (G4862) sun and  (G4155) pnigo; to strangle completely, i.e. (literally) to drown, or (figuratively) to crowd -- choke, throng. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G4155) pnigo
From  (G4862) sun and  (G4177) polites; a native of the same town, i.e. (figuratively) co-religionist (fellow-Christian) -- fellow- citizen. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G4177) polites

column7: to journey together, to come together
column9: From  (G4862) sun and  (G4198) poreuomai; to journey together; by implication, to assemble -- go with, resort. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G4198) poreuomai

column7: a drinking party, company (guests at a party)
column9: Neuter of a derivative of the alternate of  (G4844) sumpino; a drinking-party ("symposium"), i.e. (by extension) a room of guests -- company. see GREEK  (G4844) sumpino
From  (G4862) sun and  (G4245) presbuteros; a co-presbyter -- presbyter, also an elder. see GREEK  (G4245) presbuteros see GREEK  (G4862) sun

column7: to bring together, to be profitable
column8: bring together, be expedient, be profitable for.
column9: From  (G4862) sun and  (G5342) phero (including its alternate); to bear together (contribute), i.e. (literally) to collect, or (figuratively) to conduce; especially (neuter participle as a noun) advantage -- be better for, bring together, be expedient (for), be good, (be) profit(-able for). see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G5342) phero
From  (G4862) sun and  (G5346) phemi; to say jointly, i.e. Assent to -- consent unto. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G5346) phemi
From  (G4862) sun and a derivative of  (G5443) phule; a co-tribesman, i.e. Native of the same country -- countryman. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G5443) phule
From  (G4862) sun and a derivative of  (G5453) phuo; grown along with (connate), i.e. (figuratively) closely united to -- planted together. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G5453) phuo
From  (G4862) sun and  (G5453) phuo; passive, to grow jointly -- spring up with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G5453) phuo

column7: to call out with, to be in harmony, generally to agree
column9: From  (G4859) sumphonos; to be harmonious, i.e. (figuratively) to accord (be suitable, concur) or stipulate (by compact) -- agree (together, with). see GREEK  (G4859) sumphonos
From  (G4856) sumphoneo; accordance -- concord. see GREEK  (G4856) sumphoneo
From  (G4859) sumphonos; unison of sound ("symphony"), i.e. A concert of instruments (harmonious note) -- music. see GREEK  (G4859) sumphonos
From  (G4862) sun and  (G5456) phone; sounding together (alike), i.e. (figuratively) accordant (neuter as noun, agreement) -- consent. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G5456) phone
From  (G4862) sun and  (G5585) psephizo; to compute jointly -- reckon. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G5585) psephizo
From  (G4862) sun and  (G5590) psuche; co-spirited, i.e. Similar in sentiment -- like-minded. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G5590) psuche

A primary preposition denoting union; with or together (but much closer than  (G3326) meta or  (G3844) para), i.e. By association, companionship, process, resemblance, possession, instrumentality, addition, etc. -- beside, with. In composition it has similar applications, including completeness. see GREEK  (G3326) meta see GREEK  (G3844) para

column7: to lead together, bring together, come together (pass.), entertain
column9: From  (G4862) sun and  (G71) ago; to lead together, i.e. Collect or convene; specially, to entertain (hospitably) -- + accompany, assemble (selves, together), bestow, come together, gather (selves together, up, together), lead into, resort, take in. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G71) ago

column7: a bringing together,  an assembling, a synagogue
column9: From (the reduplicated form of)  (G4863) sunago; an assemblage of persons; specially, a Jewish "synagogue" (the meeting or the place); by analogy, a Christian church -- assembly, congregation, synagogue. see GREEK  (G4863) sunago
From  (G4862) sun and  (G75) agonizomai; to struggle in company with, i.e. (figuratively) to be a partner (assistant) -- strive together with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G75) agonizomai
From  (G4862) sun and  (G118) athleo; to wrestle in company with, i.e. (figuratively) to seek jointly -- labour with, strive together for. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G118) athleo
From  (G4862) sun and athroizo (to hoard); to convene -- call (gather) together. see GREEK  (G4862) sun

column7: to take up together, settle accounts
column9: From  (G4862) sun and  (G142) airo; to make up together, i.e. (figuratively) to compute (an account) -- reckon, take. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G142) airo
From  (G4862) sun and  (G164) aichmalotos; a co-captive -- fellowprisoner. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G164) aichmalotos
From  (G4862) sun and  (G190) akoloutheo; to accompany -- follow. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G190) akoloutheo
From  (G4862) sun and halizo (to throng); to accumulate, i.e. Convene -- assemble together. see GREEK  (G4862) sun
From  (G4862) sun and  (G305) anabaino; to ascend in company with -- come up with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G305) anabaino
From  (G4862) sun and  (G345) anakeimai; to recline in company with (at a meal) -- sit (down, at the table, together) with (at meat). see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G345) anakeimai

column7: to mix up together, to associate with
column9: From  (G4862) sun and a compound of  (G303) ana and  (G3396) mignumi; to mix up together, i.e. (figurative) associate with -- (have, keep) company (with). see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G303) ana see GREEK  (G3396) mignumi

column7: to lie down to rest with, to be refreshed in spirit with
column9: Middle from  (G4862) sun and  (G373) anapano; to recruit oneself in company with -- refresh with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G373) anapano
From  (G4862) sun and a derivative of  (G473) anti; to meet with; figuratively, to occur -- befall, meet. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G473) anti
From  (G4876) sunantao; a meeting with -- meet. see GREEK  (G4876) sunantao

column7: to take hold with at the side, to take a share in, generally to help
column9: From  (G4862) sun and  (G482) antilambanomai; to take hold of opposite together, i.e. Co-operate (assist) -- help. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G482) antilambanomai

column7: to lead away with, to be carried away with (pass.)
column9: From  (G4862) sun and  (G520) apago; to take off together, i.e. Transport with (seduce, passively, yield) -- carry (lead) away with, condescend. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G520) apago
From  (G4862) sun and  (G599) apothnesko; to decease (literally) in company with, or (figuratively), similarly to -- be dead (die) with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G599) apothnesko

column7: to destroy with, mid. to perish together
column9: From  (G4862) sun and  (G622) apollumi; to destroy (middle voice or passively, be slain) in company with -- perish with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G622) apollumi
From  (G4862) sun and  (G649) apostello; to despatch (on an errand) in company with -- send with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G649) apostello

From  (G4862) sun and a derivative of a compound of  (G719) harmos and  (G3004) lego (in its original sense of laying); to render close-jointed together, i.e. Organize compactly -- be fitly framed (joined) together. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G719) harmos see GREEK  (G3004) lego
From  (G4862) sun and  (G726) harpazo; to snatch together, i.e. Seize -- catch. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G726) harpazo

column7: to cause to grow together, pass. to grow together
column9: From  (G4862) sun and  (G837) auzano; to increase (grow up) together -- grow together. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G837) auzano

column7: that which binds together, a bond
column9: From  (G4862) sun and  (G1199) desmon; a joint tie, i.e. Ligament, (figuratively) uniting principle, control -- band, bond. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G1199) desmon
From  (G4862) sun and  (G1210) deo; to bind with, i.e. (passively) be a fellow-prisoner (figuratively) -- be bound with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G1210) deo

column7: to join in approving, to glorify together
column9: From  (G4862) sun and  (G1392) doxazo; to exalt to dignity in company (i.e. Similarly) with -- glorify together. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G1392) doxazo
From  (G4862) sun and  (G1401) doulos; a co-slave, i.e. Servitor or ministrant of the same master (human or divine) -- fellowservant. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G1401) doulos

column7: a running together, a concourse (esp. of a riotous gathering)
column9: From (the alternate of)  (G4936) suntrecho; a running together, i.e. (riotous) concourse -- run together. see GREEK  (G4936) suntrecho

From  (G4862) sun and  (G1453) egeiro; to rouse (from death) in company with, i.e. (figuratively) to revivify (spirtually) in resemblance to -- raise up together, rise with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G1453) egeiro

column7: a sitting together, a council, the Sanhedrin
column9: Neuter of a presumed derivative of a compound of  (G4862) sun and the base of  (G1476) hedraios; a joint session, i.e. (specially), the Jewish Sanhedrin; by analogy, a subordinate tribunal -- council. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G1476) hedraios
From a prolonged form of  (G4894) suneido; co-perception, i.e. Moral consciousness -- conscience. see GREEK  (G4894) suneido

column8: know, be privy, be aware of.
column9: From  (G4862) sun and  (G1492) eido; to see completely; used (like its primary) only in two past tenses, respectively meaning to understand or become aware, and to be conscious or (clandestinely) informed of -- consider, know, be privy, be ware of. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G1492) eido
From  (G4862) sun and  (G1510) eimi (including its various inflections); to be in company with, i.e. Present at the time -- be with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G1510) eimi
From  (G4862) sun and eimi (to go); to assemble -- gather together. see GREEK  (G4862) sun

column8: go in with, go with into.
column9: From  (G4862) sun and  (G1525) eiserchomai; to enter in company with -- go in with, go with into. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G1525) eiserchomai
From  (G4862) sun and the base of  (G1553) ekdemeo; a co-absentee from home, i.e. Fellow-traveller -- companion in travel, travel with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G1553) ekdemeo
From a compound of  (G4862) sun and  (G1586) eklegomai; chosen in company with, i.e. Co-elect (fellow Christian) -- elected together with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G1586) eklegomai
From  (G4862) sun and  (G1643) elauno; to drive together, i.e. (figuratively) exhort (to reconciliation) -- + set at one again. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G1643) elauno

column7: to testify or bear witness together with
column9: From  (G4862) sun and  (G1957) epimartureo; to testify further jointly, i.e. Unite in adding evidence -- also bear witness. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G1957) epimartureo
Middle voice from  (G4862) sun and a primary hepo (to follow); to attend (travel) in company with -- accompany. see GREEK  (G4862) sun
From  (G4904) sunergos; to be a fellow-worker, i.e. Co-operate -- help (work) with, work(-er) together. see GREEK  (G4904) sunergos

From a presumed compound of  (G4862) sun and the base of  (G2041) ergon; a co-laborer, i.e. Coadjutor -- companion in labour, (fellow-)helper(-labourer, -worker), labourer together with, workfellow. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G2041) ergon

From  (G4862) sun and  (G2064) erchomai; to convene, depart in company with, associate with, or (specially), cohabit (conjugally) -- accompany, assemble (with), come (together), come (company, go) with, resort. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G2064) erchomai
From  (G4862) sun and  (G2068) esthio (including its alternate); to take food in company with -- eat with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G2068) esthio
From  (G4920) suniemi; a mental putting together, i.e. Intelligence or (concretely) the intellect -- knowledge, understanding. see GREEK  (G4920) suniemi
From  (G4920) suniemi; mentally put (or putting) together, i.e. Sagacious -- prudent. Compare  (G5429) phronimos. see GREEK  (G4920) suniemi see GREEK  (G5429) phronimos

column8: allow, assent, be pleased, have pleasure.
column9: From  (G4862) sun and  (G2106) eudokeo; to think well of in common, i.e. Assent to, feel gratified with -- allow, assent, be pleased, have pleasure. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G2106) eudokeo

column7: to entertain together, pass. feast together
column9: From  (G4862) sun and a derivative of a presumed compound of  (G2095) eu and a derivative of  (G2192) echo (meaning to be in good condition, i.e. (by implication) to fare well, or feast); to entertain sumptuously in company with, i.e. (middle voice or passive) to revel together -- feast with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G2192) echo
From  (G4862) sun and  (G2186) ephistemi; to stand up together, i.e. To resist (or assault) jointly -- rise up together. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G2186) ephistemi

column7: to hold together, to hold fast, pass. to be seized (by illness)
column9: From  (G4862) sun and  (G2192) echo; to hold together, i.e. To compress (the ears, with a crowd or siege) or arrest (a prisoner); figuratively, to compel, perplex, afflict, preoccupy -- constrain, hold, keep in, press, lie sick of, stop, be in a strait, straiten, be taken with, throng. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G2192) echo
Middle voice from  (G4862) sun and the base of  (G2237) hedone; to rejoice in with oneself, i.e. Feel satisfaction concerning -- delight. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G2237) hedone
From a compound of  (G4862) sun and  (G2239) ethos; mutual habituation, i.e. Usage -- custom. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G2239) ethos
From  (G4862) sun and a derivative of  (G2244) helikia; a co-aged person, i.e. Alike in years -- equal. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G2244) helikia

From  (G4862) sun and  (G2290) thapto; to inter in company with, i.e. (figuratively) to assimilate spiritually (to Christ by a sepulture as to sin) -- bury with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G2290) thapto
From  (G4862) sun and thlao (to crush); to dash together, i.e. Shatter -- break. see GREEK  (G4862) sun
From  (G4862) sun and  (G2346) thlibo; to compress, i.e. Crowd on all sides -- throng. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G2346) thlibo
From  (G4862) sun and thrupto (to crumble); to crush together, i.e. (figuratively) to dispirit -- break. see GREEK  (G4862) sun
From  (G4862) sun and hiemi (to send); to put together, i.e. (mentally) to comprehend; by implication, to act piously -- consider, understand, be wise. see GREEK  (G4862) sun

column7: to commend, establish, stand near, consist
column9: Or (strengthened) sunistano (soon-is-tan'-o), or sunistemi (soon-is'-tay-mee) from  (G4862) sun and  (G2476) histemi (including its collateral forms); to set together, i.e. (by implication) to introduce (favorably), or (figuratively) to exhibit; intransitively, to stand near, or (figuratively) to constitute -- approve, commend, consist, make, stand (with). see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G2476) histemi
From  (G4862) sun and  (G3593) hodeuo; to travel in company with -- journey with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G3593) hodeuo

column7: a journey in company,  a company (of travelers)
column9: From a compound of  (G4862) sun and  (G3598) hodos ("synod"); companionship on a journey, i.e. (by implication), a caravan -- company. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G3598) hodos
From  (G4862) sun and  (G3611) oikeo; to reside together (as a family) -- dwell together. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G3611) oikeo

column7: to build together, to build up together
column9: From  (G4862) sun and  (G3618) oikodomeo; to construct, i.e. (passively) to compose (in company with other Christians, figuratively) -- build together. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G3618) oikodomeo
From  (G4862) sun and  (G3656) homileo; to converse mutually -- talk with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G3656) homileo

From  (G4862) sun and a derivative of a compound of the base of  (G3674) homou and the base of  (G3725) horion; to border together, i.e. Adjoin -- join hard. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G3725) horion
From  (G4912) sunecho; restraint, i.e. (figuratively) anxiety -- anguish, distress. see GREEK  (G4912) sunecho
From  (G4862) sun and  (G5021) tasso; to arrange jointly, i.e. (figuratively) to direct -- appoint. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G5021) tasso

column7: a joint payment (for public service), joint action, completion
column9: From  (G4931) sunteleo; entire completion, i.e. Consummation (of a dispensation) -- end. see GREEK  (G4931) sunteleo
From  (G4862) sun and  (G5055) teleo; to complete entirely; generally, to execute (literally or figuratively) -- end, finish, fulfil, make. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G5055) teleo
From  (G4862) sun and the base of  (G5114) tomoteros; to contract by cutting, i.e. (figuratively) do concisely (speedily) -- (cut) short. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G5114) tomoteros

From  (G4862) sun and  (G5083) tereo; to keep closely together, i.e. (by implication) to conserve (from ruin); mentally, to remember (and obey) -- keep, observe, preserve. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G5083) tereo

Middle voice from  (G4862) sun and  (G5087) tithemi; to place jointly, i.e. (figuratively) to consent (bargain, stipulate), concur -- agree, assent, covenant. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G5087) tithemi
Adverb from a derivative of  (G4932) suntemno; concisely (briefly) -- a few words. see GREEK  (G4932) suntemno

From  (G4862) sun and  (G5143) trecho (including its alternate); to rush together (hastily assemble) or headlong (figuratively) -- run (together, with). see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G5143) trecho

From  (G4862) sun and the base of  (G5147) tribos; to crush completely, i.e. To shatter (literally or figuratively) -- break (in pieces), broken to shivers (+ -hearted), bruise. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G5147) tribos
From  (G4937) suntribo; concussion or utter fracture (properly, concretely), i.e. Complete ruin -- destruction. see GREEK  (G4937) suntribo

column7: one brought up with, a foster brother or an intimate friend
column9: From  (G4862) sun and  (G5162) trophos (in a passive sense); a fellow-nursling, i.e. Comrade -- brought up with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G5162) trophos
From  (G4862) sun and  (G5177) tugchano; to chance together, i.e. Meet with (reach) -- come at. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G5177) tugchano

column7: happy event, Syntyche, a Christian woman at Philippi
column9: From  (G4940) suntugchano; an accident; Syntyche, a Christian female -- Syntyche. see GREEK  (G4940) suntugchano
From  (G4862) sun and  (G5271) hupokrinomai; to act hypocritically in concert with -- dissemble with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G5271) hupokrinomai

From  (G4862) sun and a derivative of a compound of  (G5259) hupo and the base of  (G2041) ergon; to be a co-auxiliary, i.e. Assist -- help together. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G5259) hupo see GREEK  (G2041) ergon

From  (G4862) sun and  (G5605) odino; to have (parturition) pangs in company (concert, simultaneously) with, i.e. (figuratively) to sympathize (in expectation of relief from suffering) -- travail in pain together. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G5605) odino
From a compound of  (G4862) sun and  (G3660) omnuo; a swearing together, i.e. (by implication) a plot -- comspiracy. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G3660) omnuo

column7: Syracuse, a large maritime city of Sicily
column9: Plural of uncertain derivation; Syracuse, the capital of Sicily -- Syracuse.

column7: Syria, a region N. and East of Pal
column9: Probably of Hebrew origin ( (H6865) Tsor); Syria (i.e. Tsyria or Tyre), a region of Asia -- Syria. see HEBREW  (H6865) Tsor
From the same as  (G4947) Suria; a Syran (i.e. Probably Tyrian), a native of Syria -- Syrian. see GREEK  (G4947) Suria

Feminine of a compound of  (G4948) Suros and the same as  (G5403) Phoinike; a Syro-phoenician woman, i.e. A female native of Phoenicia in Syria -- Syrophenician. see GREEK  (G4948) Suros see GREEK  (G5403) Phoinike

column7: shoal, Syrtis, the name of two large sandbanks on the Lybian coast
column9: From  (G4951) suro; a shoal (from the sand drawn thither by the waves), i.e. The Syrtis Major or great bay on the north coast of Africa -- quicksands. see GREEK  (G4951) suro
Probably akin to  (G138) haireomai; to trail -- drag, draw, hale. see GREEK  (G138) haireomai
From  (G4862) sun and  (G4682) sparasso; to rend completely, i.e. (by analogy) to convulse violently -- throw down. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G4682) sparasso
Neuter of a compound of  (G4862) sun and the base of  (G4591) semaino; a sign in common, i.e. Preconcerted signal -- token. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G4591) semaino
From  (G4862) sun and  (G4983) soma; of a joint body, i.e. (figuratively) a fellow-member of the Christian community -- of the same body. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G4983) soma
From a compound of  (G4862) sun and a derivative of  (G4714) stasis; a fellow-insurgent -- make insurrection with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G4714) stasis
From a derivative of  (G4921) sunistao; introductory, i.e. Recommendatory -- of commendation. see GREEK  (G4921) sunistao
From  (G4862) sun and  (G4717) stauroo; to impale in company with (literally or figuratively) -- crucify with. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G4717) stauroo
From  (G4862) sun and  (G4724) stello; to send (draw) together, i.e. Enwrap (enshroud a corpse for burial), contract (an interval) -- short, wind up. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G4724) stello
From  (G4862) sun and  (G4727) stenazo; to moan jointly, i.e. (figuratively) experience a common calamity -- groan together. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G4727) stenazo

column7: to stand in the same rank, correspond to
column9: From  (G4862) sun and  (G4748) stoicheo; to file together (as soldiers in ranks), i.e. (figuratively) to correspond to -- answer to. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G4748) stoicheo
From  (G4862) sun and  (G4757) stratiotes; a co-campaigner, i.e. (figuratively) an associate in Christian toil -- fellowsoldier. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G4757) stratiotes

column7: to twist together, to gather together (pass.)
column9: From  (G4862) sun and  (G4762) strepho; to twist together, i.e. Collect (a bundle, a crowd) -- gather. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G4762) strepho

column7: a twisting together, a concourse or conspiracy
column9: From  (G4962) sustrepho; a twisting together, i.e. (figuratively) a secret coalition, riotous crowd -- + band together, concourse. see GREEK  (G4962) sustrepho

column8: conform to, fashion self according to.
column9: From  (G4862) sun and a derivative of  (G4976) schema; to fashion alike, i.e. Conform to the same pattern (figuratively) -- conform to, fashion self according to. see GREEK  (G4862) sun see GREEK  (G4976) schema
Of Hebrew origin ( (H7941) shekar); Sychar (i.e. Shekar), a place in Palestine -- Sychar. see HEBREW  (H7941) shekar
Of Hebrew origin ( (H7927) Shkem); Sychem (i.e. Shekem), the name of a Canaanite and of a place in Palestine -- Sychem. see HEBREW  (H7927) Shkem
From  (G4969) sphazo; butchery (of animals for food or sacrifice, or (figuratively) of men (destruction)) -- slaughter. see GREEK  (G4969) sphazo
Neuter of a derivative of  (G4967) sphage; a victim (in sacrifice) -- slain beast. see GREEK  (G4967) sphage
A primary verb; to butcher (especially an animal for food or in sacrifice) or (generally) to slaughter, or (specially), to maim (violently) -- kill, slay, wound.
Neuter plural of sphodros (violent; of uncertain derivation) as adverb; vehemently, i.e. In a high degree, much -- exceeding(-ly), greatly, sore, very.
Adverb from the same as  (G4970) sphodra; very much -- exceedingly. see GREEK  (G4970) sphodra

From  (G4973) sphragis; to stamp (with a signet or private mark) for security or preservation (literally or figuratively); by implication, to keep secret, to attest -- (set a, set to) seal up, stop. see GREEK  (G4973) sphragis

Probably strengthened from  (G5420) phrasso; a signet (as fencing in or protecting from misappropriation); by implication, the stamp impressed (as a mark of privacy, or genuineness), literally or figuratively -- seal. see GREEK  (G5420) phrasso
Neuter of a presumed derivative probably of the same as sphaira (a ball, "sphere"; compare the feminine sphura, a hammer); the ankle (as globular) -- ancle bone.
Neuter of a presumed derivative of the alternate of  (G2192) echo as adverb; nigh, i.e. Nearly -- almost. see GREEK  (G2192) echo
From the alternate of  (G2192) echo; a figure (as a mode or circumstance), i.e. (by implication) external condition -- fashion. see GREEK  (G2192) echo
Apparently a primary verb; to split or sever (literally or figuratively) -- break, divide, open, rend, make a rent.
From  (G4977) schizo; a split or gap ("schism"), literally or figuratively -- division, rent, schism. see GREEK  (G4977) schizo
Diminutive of schoinos (a rush or flag-plant; of uncertain derivation); a rushlet, i.e. Grass-withe or tie (generally) -- small cord, rope.

column7: to be at leisure, to devote oneself to
column9: From  (G4981) schole; to take a holiday, i.e. Be at leisure for (by implication, devote oneself wholly to); figuratively, to be vacant (of a house) -- empty, give self. see GREEK  (G4981) schole

column7: leisure, disputation (that for which leisure is used),  school
column9: Probably feminine of a presumed derivative of the alternate of  (G2192) echo; properly, loitering (as a withholding of oneself from work) or leisure, i.e. (by implication) a "school" (as vacation from physical employment) -- school. see GREEK  (G2192) echo
From a primary sos (contraction for obsolete saos, "safe"); to save, i.e. Deliver or protect (literally or figuratively) -- heal, preserve, save (self), do well, be (make) whole.
From  (G4982) sozo; the body (as a sound whole), used in a very wide application, literally or figuratively -- bodily, body, slave. see GREEK  (G4982) sozo
From  (G4983) soma; corporeal or physical -- bodily. see GREEK  (G4983) soma
Adverb from  (G4984) somatikos; corporeally or physically -- bodily. see GREEK  (G4984) somatikos

column7: of a safe father, Sopater, a Christian from Berea
column9: From the base of  (G4982) sozo and  (G3962) pater; of a safe father; Sopatrus, a Christian -- Sopater. Compare  (G4989) Sosipatros. see GREEK  (G4982) sozo see GREEK  (G3962) pater see GREEK  (G4989) Sosipatros
From another form of  (G4673) soros; to pile up (literally or figuratively) -- heap, load. see GREEK  (G4673) soros

column7: of safe strength, Sosthenes, the name of a ruler of a synagogue and of a Christian
column9: From the base of  (G4982) sozo and that of  (G4599) sthenoo; of safe strength; Sosthenes, a Christian -- Sosthenes. see GREEK  (G4982) sozo see GREEK  (G4599) sthenoo

column7: of a safe father, Sosipater, a Christian
column9: Prolongation for  (G4986) Sopatros; Sosipatrus, a Christian -- Sosipater. see GREEK  (G4986) Sopatros
From  (G4982) sozo; a deliverer, i.e. God or Christ -- saviour. see GREEK  (G4982) sozo
Feminine of a derivative of  (G4990) soter as (properly, abstract) noun; rescue or safety (physically or morally) -- deliver, health, salvation, save, saving. see GREEK  (G4990) soter
Neuter of the same as  (G4991) soteria as (properly, concretely) noun; defender or (by implication) defence -- salvation. see GREEK  (G4991) soteria

column7: to be of sound mind, to be temperate
column8: be in right mind, be sober minded
column9: From  (G4998) sophron; to be of sound mind, i.e. Sane, (figuratively) moderate -- be in right mind, be sober (minded), soberly. see GREEK  (G4998) sophron

column7: to recall one to his senses, admonish
column8: correct, discipline, teach to be sober.
column9: From  (G4998) sophron; to make of sound mind, i.e. (figuratively) to discipline or correct -- teach to be sober. see GREEK  (G4998) sophron
From  (G4994) sophronizo; discipline, i.e. Self-control -- sound mind. see GREEK  (G4994) sophronizo
Adverb from  (G4998) sophron; with sound mind, i.e. Moderately -- soberly. see GREEK  (G4998) sophron
From  (G4998) sophron; soundness of mind, i.e. (literally) sanity or (figuratively) self-control -- soberness, sobriety. see GREEK  (G4998) sophron

From the base of  (G4982) sozo and that of  (G5424) phren; safe (sound) in mind, i.e. Self-controlled (moderate as to opinion or passion) -- discreet, sober, temperate. see GREEK  (G4982) sozo see GREEK  (G5424) phren

column7: hut, a tavern, Treis Tabernai, "Three Taverns", a stopping place on the Appian Way
column9: Plural of Latin origin; huts or wooden-walled buildings; Tabernoe -- taverns.

column7: gazelle, Tabitha (also called Dorcas), a Christian woman
column9: Of Chaldee origin (compare  (H6646) tsbiyah); the gazelle; Tabitha (i.e. Tabjetha), a Christian female -- Tabitha. see HEBREW  (H6646) tsbiyah

column7: that which has been arranged in order, a division, rank
column9: From  (G5021) tasso; something orderly in arrangement (a troop), i.e. (figuratively) a series or succession -- order. see GREEK  (G5021) tasso
From  (G5021) tasso; arranged, i.e. Appointed or stated -- set. see GREEK  (G5021) tasso
From  (G5005) talaiporos; to be wretched, i.e. Realize one's own misery -- be afflicted. see GREEK  (G5005) talaiporos
From  (G5005) talaiporos; wretchedness, i.e. Calamity -- misery. see GREEK  (G5005) talaiporos
From the base of  (G5007) talanton and a derivative of the base of  (G3984) peira; enduring trial, i.e. Miserable -- wretched. see GREEK  (G5007) talanton see GREEK  (G3984) peira

column7: worth a talent, of a talent\'s weight
column9: From  (G5007) talanton; talent-like in weight -- weight of a talent. see GREEK  (G5007) talanton

column7: a balance, that which is weighed, a talent (about 3000 shekels in weight)
column9: Neuter of a presumed derivative of the original form of tlao (to bear; equivalent to  (G5342) phero); a balance (as supporting weights), i.e. (by implication) a certain weight (and thence a coin or rather sum of money) or "talent" -- talent. see GREEK  (G5342) phero
Of Chaldee origin (compare  (H2924) taleh); the fresh, i.e. Young girl; talitha (O maiden) -- talitha. see HEBREW  (H2924) taleh

Neuter contraction of a presumed derivative of tamias (a dispenser or distributor; akin to temno, to cut); a dispensary or magazine, i.e. A chamber on the ground-floor or interior of an Oriental house (generally used for storage or privacy, a spot for retirement) -- secret chamber, closet, storehouse.
From  (G5021) tasso; regular arrangement, i.e. (in time) fixed succession (of rank or character), official dignity -- order. see GREEK  (G5021) tasso
Of uncertain derivation; depressed, i.e. (figuratively) humiliated (in circumstances or disposition) -- base, cast down, humble, of low degree (estate), lowly.

From a compound of  (G5011) tapeinos and the base of  (G5424) phren; humiliation of mind, i.e. Modesty -- humbleness of mind, humility (of mind, loneliness (of mind). see GREEK  (G5011) tapeinos see GREEK  (G5424) phren
From  (G5011) tapeinos; to depress; figuratively, to humiliate (in condition or heart) -- abase, bring low, humble (self). see GREEK  (G5011) tapeinos
From  (G5013) tapeinoo; depression (in rank or feeling) -- humiliation, be made low, low estate, vile. see GREEK  (G5013) tapeinoo
Of uncertain affinity; to stir or agitate (roil water) -- trouble.
Feminine from  (G5015) tarasso; disturbance, i.e. (of water) roiling, or (of a mob) sedition -- trouble(-ing). see GREEK  (G5015) tarasso
Masculine from  (G5015) tarasso; a disturbance, i.e. (popular) tumult -- stir. see GREEK  (G5015) tarasso
From  (G5019) Tarsos; a Tarsean, i.e. Native of Tarsus -- of Tarsus. see GREEK  (G5019) Tarsos
Perhaps the same as tarsos (a flat basket); Tarsus, a place in Asia Minor -- Tarsus.
From Tartaros (the deepest abyss of Hades); to incarcerate in eternal torment -- cast down to hell.

column7: to draw up in order, arrange
column9: A prolonged form of a primary verb (which latter appears only in certain tenses); to arrange in an orderly manner, i.e. Assign or dispose (to a certain position or lot) -- addict, appoint, determine, ordain, set.
Apparently a primary word (compare  (H8450) towr, "steer"); a bullock -- bull, ox. see HEBREW  (H8450) towr

Nominative or accusative case neuter plural of  (G3778) houtos; these things -- + afterward, follow, + hereafter, X him, the same, so, such, that, then, these, they, this, those, thus. see GREEK  (G3778) houtos
Neuter plural of  (G3588) ho and  (G846) autos as adverb; in the same way -- even thus, (manner) like, so. see GREEK  (G3588) ho see GREEK  (G846) autos
And tautas (tow'-tas) dative case and accusative case feminine plural respectively of  (G3778) houtos; (to or with or by, etc.) These -- hence, that, then, these, those. see GREEK  (G3778) houtos

And tauten (tow'-tane), and tautes (tow'-tace) dative case, accusative case and genitive case respectively of the feminine singular of  (G3778) houtos; (towards or of) this -- her, + hereof, it, that, + thereby, the (same), this (same). see GREEK  (G3778) houtos
Feminine from  (G2290) thapto; burial (the act) -- X bury. see GREEK  (G2290) thapto
Masculine from  (G2290) thapto; a grave (the place of interment) -- sepulchre, tomb. see GREEK  (G2290) thapto
As if neuter plural of  (G5036) tachus (adverbially); shortly, i.e. (figuratively) possibly -- peradventure(-haps). see GREEK  (G5036) tachus
Adverb from  (G5036) tachus; briefly, i.e. (in time) speedily, or (in manner) rapidly -- hastily, quickly, shortly, soon, suddenly. see GREEK  (G5036) tachus
From  (G5034) tachos; curt, i.e. Impending -- shortly, swift. see GREEK  (G5034) tachos

Neuter singular of the comparative of  (G5036) tachus (as adverb); more swiftly, i.e. (in manner) more rapidly, or (in time) more speedily -- out (run), quickly, shortly, sooner. see GREEK  (G5036) tachus

Neuter plural of the superlative of  (G5036) tachus (as adverb); most quickly, i.e. (with  (G5613) hos prefixed) as soon as possible -- + with all speed. see GREEK  (G5036) tachus see GREEK  (G5613) hos
From the same as  (G5036) tachus; a brief space (of time), i.e. (with  (G1722) en prefixed) in haste -- + quickly, + shortly, + speedily. see GREEK  (G5036) tachus see GREEK  (G1722) en
Neuter singular of  (G5036) tachus (as adverb); shortly, i.e. Without delay, soon, or (by surprise) suddenly, or (by implication, of ease) readily -- lightly, quickly. see GREEK  (G5036) tachus
Of uncertain affinity; fleet, i.e. (figuratively) prompt or ready -- swift.

A primary particle (enclitic) of connection or addition; both or also (properly, as correlation of  (G2532) kai) -- also, and, both, even, then, whether. Often used in composition, usually as the latter participle. see GREEK  (G2532) kai
Akin to the base of  (G5088) tikto; a wall (as formative of a house) -- wall. see GREEK  (G5088) tikto
Neuter of a presumed derivative of tekmar (a goal or fixed limit); a token (as defining a fact), i.e. Criterion of certainty -- infallible proof.
Diminutive of  (G5043) teknon; an infant, i.e. (plural figuratively) darlings (Christian converts) -- little children. see GREEK  (G5043) teknon
From a compound of  (G5043) teknon and the base of  (G1096) ginomai; to be a child-bearer, i.e. Parent (mother) -- bear children. see GREEK  (G5043) teknon see GREEK  (G1096) ginomai
From the same as  (G5041) teknogoneo; childbirth (parentage), i.e. (by implication) maternity (the performance of maternal duties) -- childbearing. see GREEK  (G5041) teknogoneo
From the base of  (G5098) timoria; a child (as produced) -- child, daughter, son. see GREEK  (G5098) timoria
From a compound of  (G5043) teknon and  (G5142) trepho; to be a childrearer, i.e. Fulfil the duties of a female parent -- bring up children. see GREEK  (G5043) teknon see GREEK  (G5142) trepho
From the base of  (G5098) timoria; an artificer (as producer of fabrics), i.e. (specially), a craftsman in wood -- carpenter. see GREEK  (G5098) timoria

column7: having reached its end, complete,  perfect
column9: From  (G5056) telos; complete (in various applications of labor, growth, mental and moral character, etc.); neuter (as noun, with  (G3588) ho) completeness -- of full age, man, perfect. see GREEK  (G5056) telos see GREEK  (G3588) ho
From  (G5046) teleios; (the state) completeness (mentally or morally) -- perfection(-ness). see GREEK  (G5046) teleios

column7: to bring to an end, to complete, perfect
column9: From  (G5046) teleios; to complete, i.e. (literally) accomplish, or (figuratively) consummate (in character) -- consecrate, finish, fulfil, make) perfect. see GREEK  (G5046) teleios
Adverb from  (G5046) teleios; completely, i.e. (of hope) without wavering -- to the end. see GREEK  (G5046) teleios
From  (G5448) phusioo; (the act) completion, i.e. (of prophecy) verification, or (of expiation) absolution -- perfection, performance. see GREEK  (G5448) phusioo
From  (G5048) teleioo; a completer, i.e. Consummater -- finisher. see GREEK  (G5048) teleioo

column7: to bring fruit to perfection, to bear perfect offspring
column8: produce maturity, bring fruit to perfection.
column9: From a compound of  (G5056) telos and  (G5342) phero; to be a bearer to completion (maturity), i.e. To ripen fruit (figuratively) -- bring fruit to perfection. see GREEK  (G5056) telos see GREEK  (G5342) phero

column7: to complete, to come to an end, to die
column9: From a presumed derivative of  (G5055) teleo; to finish life (by implication, of  (G979) bios), i.e. Expire (demise) -- be dead, decease, die. see GREEK  (G5055) teleo see GREEK  (G979) bios
From  (G5053) teleutao; decease -- death. see GREEK  (G5053) teleutao

column7: to bring to an end, complete, fulfill
column9: From  (G5056) telos; to end, i.e. Complete, execute, conclude, discharge (a debt) -- accomplish, make an end, expire, fill up, finish, go over, pay, perform. see GREEK  (G5056) telos

From a primary tello (to set out for a definite point or goal); properly, the point aimed at as a limit, i.e. (by implication) the conclusion of an act or state (termination (literally, figuratively or indefinitely), result (immediate, ultimate or prophetic), purpose); specially, an impost or levy (as paid) -- + continual, custom, end(-ing), finally, uttermost. Compare  (G5411) phoros. see GREEK  (G5411) phoros
From  (G5056) telos and  (G5608) oneomai; a tax-farmer, i.e. Collector of public revenue -- publican. see GREEK  (G5056) telos see GREEK  (G5608) oneomai
Neuter of a presumed derivative of  (G5057) telones; a tax-gatherer's place of business -- receipt of custom. see GREEK  (G5057) telones
Of uncertain affinity; a prodigy or omen -- wonder.

column7: third, Tertius, a Christian to whom Paul dictated Romans
column9: Of Latin origin; third; Tertius, a Christian -- Tertius.
Of uncertain derivation; Tertullus, a Roman -- Tertullus.
The decade of  (G5064) tessares; forty -- forty. see GREEK  (G5064) tessares
From  (G5062) tessarakonta and  (G2094) etos; of forty years of age -- (+ full, of) forty years (old). see GREEK  (G5062) tessarakonta see GREEK  (G2094) etos
Or neuter tessara (tes'-sar-ah) a plural number; four -- four.
From  (G5064) tessares and  (G2532) kai and  (G1182) dekatos; fourteenth -- fourteenth. see GREEK  (G5064) tessares see GREEK  (G2532) kai see GREEK  (G1182) dekatos
From  (G5064) tessares; pertaining to the fourth day -- four days. see GREEK  (G5064) tessares
Ordinal from  (G5064) tessares; fourth -- four(-th). see GREEK  (G5064) tessares

column7: a tetrarch (the governor of a fourth part of a region)
column9: From  (G5064) tessares and  (G1137) gonia; four-cornered, i.e. Square -- foursquare. see GREEK  (G5064) tessares see GREEK  (G1137) gonia

column7: a group of four, a quaternion (a guard of four soldiers)
column9: Neuter of a presumed derivative of tetras (a tetrad; from  (G5064) tessares); a quaternion or squad (picket) of four Roman soldiers -- quaternion. see GREEK  (G5064) tessares
From the multiplicative adverb of  (G5064) tessares and  (G5507) chilioi; four times a thousand -- four thousand. see GREEK  (G5064) tessares see GREEK  (G5507) chilioi

Plural from  (G5064) tessares and  (G1540) hekaton; four hundred -- four hundred. Plural from  (G5064) tessares and  (G1540) hekaton; four hundred -- four hundred. see GREEK  (G5064) tessares see GREEK  (G1540) hekaton
Neuter of a compound of  (G5064) tessares and  (G3376) men; a four months' space -- four months. see GREEK  (G5064) tessares see GREEK  (G3376) men
From  (G5064) tessares and a derivative of the base of  (G4118) pleistos; quadruple -- fourfold. see GREEK  (G5064) tessares see GREEK  (G4118) pleistos
From  (G5064) tessares and  (G4228) pous; a quadruped -- fourfooted beast. see GREEK  (G5064) tessares see GREEK  (G4228) pous
From  (G5076) tetrarches; to be a tetrarch -- (be) tetrarch. see GREEK  (G5076) tetrarches
From  (G5064) tessares and  (G757) archo; the ruler of a fourth part of a country ("tetrarch") -- tetrarch. see GREEK  (G5064) tessares see GREEK  (G757) archo
From tephra (ashes); to incinerate, i.e. Consume -- turn to ashes.
From the base of  (G5088) tikto; art (as productive), i.e. (specially), a trade, or (generally) skill -- art, craft, occupation. see GREEK  (G5088) tikto
From  (G5078) techne; an artisan; figuratively, a founder (Creator) -- builder, craftsman. see GREEK  (G5078) techne
Apparently a primary verb; to liquefy -- melt.
Adverb from a compound of a derivative of  (G5056) telos and  (G827) auge; in a far-shining manner, i.e. Plainly -- clearly. see GREEK  (G5056) telos see GREEK  (G827) auge

column7: such as this, of persons so old, of things so great
column9: Or feminine telikaute (tay-lik-ow'-tay) from a compound of  (G3588) ho with  (G2245) helikos and  (G3778) houtos; such as this, i.e. (in (figurative) magnitude) so vast -- so great, so mighty. see GREEK  (G3588) ho see GREEK  (G2245) helikos see GREEK  (G3778) houtos

From teros (a watch; perhaps akin to  (G2334) theoreo); to guard (from loss or injury, properly, by keeping the eye upon; and thus differing from  (G5442) phulasso, which is properly to prevent escaping; and from  (G2892) koustodia, which implies a fortress or full military lines of apparatus), i.e. To note (a prophecy; figuratively, to fulfil a command); by implication, to detain (in custody; figuratively, to maintain); by extension, to withhold (for personal ends; figuratively, to keep unmarried); by extension, to withhold (for personal ends; figuratively, to keep unmarried) -- hold fast, keep(- er), (pre-, re-)serve, watch. see GREEK  (G2334) theoreo see GREEK  (G5442) phulasso see GREEK  (G2892) koustodia
From  (G5083) tereo; a watching, i.e. (figuratively) observance, or (concretely) a prison -- hold. see GREEK  (G5083) tereo

column7: Tiberias, a city of Galilee, also another name for the Sea of Galilee
column9: From  (G5086) Tiberios; Tiberias, the name of a town and a lake in Palestine -- Tiberias. see GREEK  (G5086) Tiberios
Of Latin origin; probably pertaining to the river Tiberis or Tiber; Tiberius, a Roman emperor -- Tiberius.

A prolonged form of a primary theo (theh'-o) (which is used only as alternate in certain tenses) to place (in the widest application, literally and figuratively; properly, in a passive or horizontal posture, and thus different from  (G2476) histemi, which properly denotes an upright and active position, while  (G2749) keimai is properly reflexive and utterly prostrate) -- + advise, appoint, bow, commit, conceive, give, X kneel down, lay (aside, down, up), make, ordain, purpose, put, set (forth), settle, sink down. see GREEK  (G2476) histemi see GREEK  (G2749) keimai

A strengthened form of a primary teko tek'-o (which is used only as alternate in certain tenses); to produce (from seed, as a mother, a plant, the earth, etc.), literally or figuratively -- bear, be born, bring forth, be delivered, be in travail.
Perhaps akin to the alternate of  (G138) haireomai, and thus to  (G4951) suro; to pull off -- pluck. see GREEK  (G4951) suro see GREEK  (G138) haireomai
Probably of Chaldee origin (compare  (H2931) tame'); Timoeus (i.e. Timay), an Israelite -- Timaeus. see HEBREW  (H2931) tame'

column7: to fix the value, to price
column9: From  (G5093) timios; to prize, i.e. Fix a valuation upon; by implication, to revere -- honour, value. see GREEK  (G5093) timios

From  (G5099) tino; a value, i.e. Money paid, or (concretely and collectively) valuables; by analogy, esteem (especially of the highest degree), or the dignity itself -- honour, precious, price, some. see GREEK  (G5099) tino

Including the comparative timioteros (tim-ee-o'-ter-os), and the superlative timiotatos (tim-ee-o'-tat-os) from  (G5092) time; valuable, i.e. (objectively) costly, or (subjectively) honored, esteemed, or (figuratively) beloved -- dear, honourable, (more, most) precious, had in reputation. see GREEK  (G5092) time
From  (G5093) timios; expensiveness, i.e. (by implication) magnificence -- costliness. see GREEK  (G5093) timios
From  (G5092) time and  (G2316) theos; dear to God; Timotheus, a Christian -- Timotheus, Timothy. see GREEK  (G5092) time see GREEK  (G2316) theos
From  (G5092) time; valuable; Timon, a Christian -- Timon. see GREEK  (G5092) time
From a comparative of  (G5092) time and ouros (a guard); properly, to protect one's honor, i.e. To avenge (inflict a penalty) -- punish. see GREEK  (G5092) time
From  (G5097) timoreo; vindication, i.e. (by implication) a penalty -- punishment. see GREEK  (G5097) timoreo

column7: to pay, to pay a penalty
column9: Strengthened for a primary tio (tee'-o) (which is only used as an alternate in certain tenses) to pay a price, i.e. As a penalty -- be punished with.

An enclitic indefinite pronoun; some or any person or object -- a (kind of), any (man, thing, thing at all), certain (thing), divers, he (every) man, one (X thing), ought, + partly, some (man, -body, - thing, -what), (+ that no-)thing, what(-soever), X wherewith, whom(-soever), whose(-soever).

column8: every man, how much, which, whom
column9: Probably emphatic of  (G5100) tis; an interrogative pronoun, who, which or what (in direct or indirect questions) -- every man, how (much), + no(-ne, thing), what (manner, thing), where (-by, -fore, -of, -unto, - with, -withal), whether, which, who(-m, -se), why. see GREEK  (G5100) tis
Of Latin origin; a titulus or "title" (placard) -- title.
Of Latin origin but uncertain significance; Titus, a Christian -- Titus.

column7: an enclitic particle of asseveration used as a prefix or suff. in the N.T
column9: Probably for the dative case of  (G3588) ho; an enclitic particle of asseveration by way of contrast; in sooth -- (used only with other particles in the comparative, as  (G2544) kaitoige,  (G3305) mentoi,  (G5105) toigaroun,  (G5106) toinun, etc.) see GREEK  (G3588) ho see GREEK  (G2544) kaitoige see GREEK  (G3305) mentoi see GREEK  (G5105) toigaroun see GREEK  (G5106) toinun
From  (G5104) toi and  (G1063) gar and  (G3767) oun; truly for then, i.e. Consequently -- there-(where-)fore. see GREEK  (G5104) toi see GREEK  (G1063) gar see GREEK  (G3767) oun
From  (G5104) toi and  (G3568) nun; truly now, i.e. Accordingly -- then, therefore. see GREEK  (G5104) toi see GREEK  (G3568) nun
(including the other inflections); from a derivative of  (G5104) toi and  (G1161) de; such-like then, i.e. So great -- such. see GREEK  (G1161) de

(including the other inflections); from  (G5104) toi and  (G3778) houtos; truly this, i.e. Of this sort (to denote character or individuality) -- like, such (an one). see GREEK  (G5104) toi see GREEK  (G3778) houtos
Another form of  (G5038) teichos; a wall -- wall. see GREEK  (G5038) teichos

column7: a bringing forth, birth, interest, usury
column9: From the base of  (G5088) tikto; interest on money loaned (as a produce) -- usury. see GREEK  (G5088) tikto

column7: to have courage, to be bold
column9: From tolma (boldness; probably itself from the base of  (G5056) telos through the idea of extreme conduct); to venture (objectively or in act; while  (G2292) tharrheo is rather subjective or in feeling); by implication, to be courageous -- be bold, boldly, dare, durst. see GREEK  (G5056) telos see GREEK  (G2292) tharrheo
Neuter of the compound of a derivative of the base of  (G5111) tolmao (as adverb); more daringly, i.e. With greater confidence than otherwise -- the more boldly.
From  (G5111) tolmao; a daring (audacious) man -- presumptuous. see GREEK  (G5111) tolmao

Comparative of a derivative of the primary temno (to cut; more comprehensive or decisive than  (G2875) kopto, as if by a single stroke; whereas that implies repeated blows, like hacking); more keen -- sharper. see GREEK  (G2875) kopto
From the base of  (G5088) tikto; a bow (apparently as the simplest fabric) -- bow. see GREEK  (G5088) tikto
Neuter of a presumed derivative (alternately) of topazos (a "topaz"; of uncertain origin); a gem, probably the chrysolite -- topaz.

Apparently a primary word; a spot (general in space, but limited by occupancy; whereas  (G5561) chora is a large but participle locality), i.e. Location (as a position, home, tract, etc.); figuratively, condition, opportunity; specially, a scabbard -- coast, licence, place, X plain, quarter, + rock, room, where. see GREEK  (G5561) chora

column7: so great, so much, pl. so many
column8: as large, so great, this many.
column9: From tosos (so much; apparently from  (G3588) ho and  (G3739) hos) and  (G3778) houtos (including its variations); so vast as this, i.e. Such (in quantity, amount, number of space) -- as large, so great (long, many, much), these many. see GREEK  (G3588) ho see GREEK  (G3739) hos see GREEK  (G3778) houtos
From (the neuter of)  (G3588) ho and  (G3753) hote; the when, i.e. At the time that (of the past or future, also in consecution) -- that time, then. see GREEK  (G3753) hote see GREEK  (G3588) ho
Properly, the genitive case of  (G3588) ho; sometimes used for  (G5127) toutou; of this person -- his. see GREEK  (G3588) ho see GREEK  (G5127) toutou
Contraction for the neuter of  (G3588) ho and  (G1726) enantion; on the contrary -- contrariwise. see GREEK  (G3588) ho see GREEK  (G1726) enantion
Contraction for the neuter of  (G3588) ho and  (G3686) onoma; the name (is) -- named. see GREEK  (G3588) ho see GREEK  (G3686) onoma
Contraction for  (G5124) touto and  (G2076) esti; that is -- that is (to say). see GREEK  (G2076) esti see GREEK  (G5124) touto

Neuter singular nominative or accusative case of  (G3778) houtos; that thing -- here (-unto), it, partly, self(-same), so, that (intent), the same, there(-fore, -unto), this, thus, where(-fore). see GREEK  (G3778) houtos
Dative case plural masculine or neuter of  (G3778) houtos; to (for, in, with or by) these (persons or things) -- such, them, there(-in, -with), these, this, those. see GREEK  (G3778) houtos
Accusative case singular masculine of  (G3778) houtos; this (person, as objective of verb or preposition) -- him, the same, that, this. see GREEK  (G3778) houtos

Genitive case singular masculine or neuter of  (G3778) houtos; of (from or concerning) this (person or thing) -- here(-by), him, it, + such manner of, that, thence(-forth), thereabout, this, thus. see GREEK  (G3778) houtos
Accusative case plural masculine of  (G3778) houtos; these (persons, as objective of verb or preposition) -- such, them, these, this. see GREEK  (G3778) houtos
Dative case singular masculine or neuter of  (G3778) houtos; to (in, with or by) this (person or thing) -- here(-by, -in), him, one, the same, there(-in), this. see GREEK  (G3778) houtos
Genitive case plural masculine or neuter of  (G3778) houtos; of (from or concerning) these (persons or things) -- such, their, these (things), they, this sort, those. see GREEK  (G3778) houtos
From the base of  (G5176) trogo; a he-goat (as a gnawer) -- goat. see GREEK  (G5176) trogo

Probably contracted from  (G5064) tessares and  (G3979) peze; a table or stool (as being four-legged), usually for food (figuratively, a meal); also a counter for money (figuratively, a broker's office for loans at interest) -- bank, meat, table. see GREEK  (G5064) tessares see GREEK  (G3979) peze
From  (G5132) trapeza; a money-broker or banker -- exchanger. see GREEK  (G5132) trapeza

From the base of titrosko (to wound; akin to the base of  (G2352) thrauo,  (G5147) tribos,  (G5149) trizo, etc.); a wound -- wound. see GREEK  (G2352) thrauo see GREEK  (G5147) tribos see GREEK  (G5149) trizo
From  (G5134) trauma; to inflict a wound -- wound. see GREEK  (G5134) trauma

column7: to take by the throat, to overthrow
column9: From  (G5137) trachelos; to seize by the throat or neck, i.e. To expose the gullet of a victim for killing (generally, to lay bare) -- opened. see GREEK  (G5137) trachelos
Probably from  (G5143) trecho (through the idea of mobility); the throat (neck), i.e. (figuratively) life -- neck. see GREEK  (G5143) trecho
Perhaps strengthened from the base of  (G4486) rhegnumi (as if jagged by rents); uneven, rocky (reefy) -- rock, rough. see GREEK  (G4486) rhegnumi

column7: Trachonitis, a rough region South of Damascus
column9: From a derivative of  (G5138) trachus; rough district; Trachonitis, a region of Syria -- Trachonitis. see GREEK  (G5138) trachus
Or neuter tria (tree'-ah) a primary (plural) number; "three" -- three.
Strengthened from a primary treo (to "dread", "terrify"); to "tremble" or fear -- be afraid, trembling.

column7: to make to grow, to nourish, feed
column9: A primary verb (properly, threpho; but perhaps strengthened from the base of  (G5157) trope through the idea of convolution); properly, to stiffen, i.e. Fatten (by implication, to cherish (with food, etc.), pamper, rear) -- bring up, feed, nourish. see GREEK  (G5157) trope

Apparently a primary verb (properly, threcho; compare  (G2359) thrix); which uses dremo drem'-o (the base of  (G1408) dromos) as alternate in certain tenses; to run or walk hastily (literally or figuratively) -- have course, run. see GREEK  (G2359) thrix see GREEK  (G1408) dromos
The decade of  (G5140) treis; thirty -- thirty. see GREEK  (G5140) treis
Plural from  (G5140) treis and  (G1540) hekaton; three hundred -- three hundred. see GREEK  (G5140) treis see GREEK  (G1540) hekaton

From  (G5140) treis and  (G956) belos; properly, a crow-foot (three-pronged obstruction in war), i.e. (by analogy) a thorny plant (caltrop) -- brier, thistle. see GREEK  (G5140) treis see GREEK  (G956) belos
From tribo (to "rub"; akin to teiro, truo, and the base of  (G5131) tragos,  (G5134) trauma); a rut or worn track -- path. see GREEK  (G5131) tragos see GREEK  (G5134) trauma
From a compound of  (G5140) treis and  (G2094) etos; a three years' period (triennium) -- space of three years. see GREEK  (G5140) treis see GREEK  (G2094) etos

column7: to cry, chirp, to grind the teeth
column9: Apparently a primary verb; to creak (squeak), i.e. (by analogy) to grate the teeth (in frenzy) -- gnash.
Neuter of a compound of  (G5140) treis and  (G3376) men as noun; a three months' space -- three months. see GREEK  (G5140) treis see GREEK  (G3376) men
Adverb from  (G5140) treis; three times -- three times, thrice. see GREEK  (G5140) treis
Neuter of a compound of  (G5140) treis and  (G4721) stege as noun; a third roof (story) -- third loft. see GREEK  (G5140) treis see GREEK  (G4721) stege
From  (G5151) tris and  (G5507) chilioi; three times a thousand -- three thousand. see GREEK  (G5151) tris see GREEK  (G5507) chilioi
Ordinal from  (G5140) treis; third; neuter (as noun) a third part, or (as adverb) a (or the) third time, thirdly -- third(-ly). see GREEK  (G5140) treis
From  (G2359) thrix; hairy, i.e. Made of hair (mohair) -- of hair. see GREEK  (G2359) thrix
From  (G5141) tremo; a "trembling", i.e. Quaking with fear -- + tremble(-ing). see GREEK  (G5141) tremo
From an apparently primary trepo to turn; a turn ("trope"), i.e. Revolution (figuratively, variation) -- turning.

From the same as  (G5157) trope; a turn, i.e. (by implication) mode or style (especially with preposition or relative prefix as adverb, like); figuratively, deportment or character -- (even) as, conversation, (+ like) manner, (+ by any) means, way. see GREEK  (G5157) trope
From  (G5158) tropos and  (G5409) phoreo; to endure one's habits -- suffer the manners. see GREEK  (G5158) tropos see GREEK  (G5409) phoreo
From  (G5142) trepho; nourishment (literally or figuratively); by implication, rations (wages) -- food, meat. see GREEK  (G5142) trepho
From  (G5160) trophe; nutritive; Trophimus, a Christian -- Trophimus. see GREEK  (G5160) trophe
From  (G5142) trepho; a nourisher, i.e. Nurse -- nurse. see GREEK  (G5142) trepho

column7: the track of a wheel, a track, path
column9: From  (G5164) trochos; a track (as a wheel-rut), i.e. (figuratively) a course of conduct -- path. see GREEK  (G5164) trochos
From  (G5143) trecho; a wheel (as a runner), i.e. (figuratively) a circuit of physical effects -- course. see GREEK  (G5143) trecho
Neuter of a presumed derivative of uncertain affinity; a bowl -- dish.
From a derivative of trugo (to dry) meaning ripe fruit (as if dry); to collect the vintage -- gather.
From truzo (to murmur; akin to  (G5149) trizo, but denoting a duller sound); a turtle-dove (as cooing) -- turtle-dove. see GREEK  (G5149) trizo

From a derivative of truo (to wear away; akin to the base of  (G5134) trauma,  (G5147) tribos and  (G5176) trogo); an orifice, i.e. Needle's eye -- eye. Compare  (G5169) trupema. see GREEK  (G5169) trupema see GREEK  (G5134) trauma see GREEK  (G5147) tribos see GREEK  (G5176) trogo
From a derivative of the base of  (G5168) trumalia; an aperture, i.e. A needle's eye -- eye. see GREEK  (G5168) trumalia
From  (G5172) truphe; luxurious; Tryphoena, a Christian woman -- Tryphena. see GREEK  (G5172) truphe
From  (G5172) truphe; to indulge in luxury -- live in pleasure. see GREEK  (G5172) truphe
From thrupto (to break up or (figuratively) enfeeble, especially the mind and body by indulgence); effeminacy, i.e. Luxury or debauchery -- delicately, riot.
From  (G5172) truphe; luxuriating; Tryphosa, a Christian female -- Tryphosa. see GREEK  (G5172) truphe

column7: Troas, a city near the Hellespont (i.e. Dardanelles)
column9: From Tros (a Trojan); the Troad (or plain of Troy), i.e. Troas, a place in Asia Minor -- Troas.
Of uncertain derivation; Trogyllium, a place in Asia Minor -- Trogyllium.

Probably strengthened from a collateral form of the base of  (G5134) trauma and  (G5147) tribos through the idea of corrosion or wear; or perhaps rather of a base of  (G5167) trugon and  (G5149) trizo through the idea of a craunching sound; to gnaw or chew, i.e. (generally) to eat -- eat. see GREEK  (G5167) trugon see GREEK  (G5149) trizo see GREEK  (G5134) trauma see GREEK  (G5147) tribos

column7: to hit, hit upon, meet, happen
column9: Probably for an obsolete tucho (for which the middle voice of another alternate teucho (to make ready or bring to pass) is used in certain tenses; akin to the base of  (G5088) tikto through the idea of effecting; properly, to affect; or (specially), to hit or light upon (as a mark to be reached), i.e. (transitively) to attain or secure an object or end, or (intransitively) to happen (as if meeting with); but in the latter application only impersonal (with  (G1487) ei), i.e. Perchance; or (present participle) as adjective, usual (as if commonly met with, with  (G3756) ou, extraordinary), neuter (as adverb) perhaps; or (with another verb) as adverb, by accident (as it were) -- be, chance, enjoy, little, obtain, X refresh...self, + special. Compare  (G5180) tupto. see GREEK  (G5180) tupto see GREEK  (G5088) tikto see GREEK  (G1487) ei see GREEK  (G3756) ou

column7: to beat a drum, to torture by beating
column9: From a derivative of  (G5180) tupto (meaning a drum, "tympanum"); to stretch on an instrument of torture resembling a drum, and thus beat to death -- torture. see GREEK  (G5180) tupto

From  (G5180) tupto; a die (as struck), i.e. (by implication) a stamp or scar; by analogy, a shape, i.e. A statue, (figuratively) style or resemblance; specially, a sampler ("type"), i.e. A model (for imitation) or instance (for warning) -- en-(ex-)ample, fashion, figure, form, manner, pattern, print. see GREEK  (G5180) tupto

A primary verb (in a strengthened form); to "thump", i.e. Cudgel or pummel (properly, with a stick or bastinado), but in any case by repeated blows; thus differing from  (G3817) paio and  (G3960) patasso, which denote a (usually single) blow with the hand or any instrument, or  (G4141) plesso with the fist (or a hammer), or  (G4474) rhapizo with the palm; as well as from  (G5177) tugchano, an accidental collision); by implication, to punish; figuratively, to offend (the conscience) -- beat, smite, strike, wound. see GREEK  (G3817) paio see GREEK  (G3960) patasso see GREEK  (G4141) plesso see GREEK  (G4474) rhapizo see GREEK  (G5177) tugchano
A provincial form of the derivative of the base of  (G2962) kurios; a "tyrant"; Tyrannus, an Ephesian -- Tyrannus. see GREEK  (G2962) kurios
From turbe (Latin turba, a crowd; akin to  (G2351) thorubos); to make "turbid", i.e. Disturb -- trouble. see GREEK  (G2351) thorubos

column7: a Tyrian, an inhabitant of Tyre
column9: From  (G5184) Turos; a Tyrian, i.e. Inhabitant of Tyrus -- of Tyre. see GREEK  (G5184) Turos
Of Hebrew origin ( (H6865) Tsor): Tyrus (i.e. Tsor), a place in Palestine -- Tyre. see HEBREW  (H6865) Tsor
From,  (G5187) tuphoo; opaque (as if smoky), i.e. (by analogy) blind (physically or mentally) -- blind. see GREEK  (G5187) tuphoo
From  (G5185) tuphlos; to make blind, i.e. (figuratively) to obscure -- blind. see GREEK  (G5185) tuphlos
From a derivative of  (G5188) tupho; to envelop with smoke, i.e. (figuratively) to inflate with self-conceit -- high-minded, be lifted up with pride, be proud. see GREEK  (G5188) tupho
Apparently a primary verb; to make a smoke, i.e. Slowly consume without flame -- smoke.
From a derivative of  (G5188) tupho; stormy (as if smoky) -- tempestuous. see GREEK  (G5188) tupho
From a derivative of  (G5177) tugchano; fortuitous, i.e. Fortunate; Tychicus, a Christian -- Tychicus. see GREEK  (G5177) tugchano
From  (G5192) huakinthos; "hyacinthine" or "jacinthine", i.e. Deep blue -- jacinth. see GREEK  (G5192) huakinthos

column8: jacinth, a deep blue colored gem
column9: Of uncertain derivation; the "hyacinth" or "jacinth", i.e. Some gem of a deep blue color, probably the zirkon -- jacinth.
From  (G5194) hualos; glassy, i.e. Transparent -- of glass. see GREEK  (G5194) hualos
Perhaps from the same as  (G5205) huetos (as being transparent like rain); glass -- glass. see GREEK  (G5205) huetos

column7: to run riot, to outrage, insult
column9: From  (G5196) hubris; to exercise violence, i.e. Abuse -- use despitefully, reproach, entreat shamefully (spitefully). see GREEK  (G5196) hubris

column7: wantonness, insolence, an act of wanton violence
column9: From  (G5228) huper; insolence (as over-bearing), i.e. Insult, injury -- harm, hurt, reproach. see GREEK  (G5228) huper
From  (G5195) hubrizo; an insulter, i.e. Maltreater -- despiteful, injurious. see GREEK  (G5195) hubrizo
From  (G5199) hugies; to have sound health, i.e. Be well (in body); figuratively, to be uncorrupt (true in doctrine) -- be in health, (be safe and) sound, (be) whole(-some). see GREEK  (G5199) hugies
From the base of  (G837) auzano; healthy, i.e. Well (in body); figuratively, true (in doctrine) -- sound, whole. see GREEK  (G837) auzano
From the base of  (G5205) huetos; wet (as if with rain), i.e. (by implication) sappy (fresh) -- green. see GREEK  (G5205) huetos

column7: a water pot, a pot or jar
column9: From  (G5204) hudor; a water-jar, i.e. Receptacle for family supply -- water-pot. see GREEK  (G5204) hudor
From a compound of  (G5204) hudor and a derivative of  (G4095) pino; to be a water-drinker, i.e. To abstain from vinous beverages -- drink water. see GREEK  (G5204) hudor see GREEK  (G4095) pino
From a compound of  (G5204) hudor and a derivative of  (G3700) optanomai (as if looking watery); to be "dropsical" -- have the dropsy. see GREEK  (G5204) hudor see GREEK  (G3700) optanomai
And genitive case, hudatos (hoo'-dat-os), etc. From the base of  (G5205) huetos; water (as if rainy) literally or figuratively -- water. see GREEK  (G5205) huetos
From a primary huo (to rain); rain, especially a shower -- rain.

From a presumed compound of  (G5207) huios and a derivative of  (G5087) tithemi; the placing as a son, i.e. Adoption (figuratively, Christian sonship in respect to God) -- adoption (of children, of sons). see GREEK  (G5207) huios see GREEK  (G5087) tithemi
Apparently a primary word; a "son" (sometimes of animals), used very widely of immediate, remote or figuratively, kinship -- child, foal, son.
Perhaps akin to  (G3586) xulon; a forest, i.e. (by implication) fuel -- matter. see GREEK  (G3586) xulon
Accusative case of  (G5210) humeis; you (as the objective of a verb or preposition) -- ye, you (+ -ward), your (+ own). see GREEK  (G5210) humeis
Irregular plural of  (G4771) su; you (as subjective of verb) -- ye (yourselves), you. see GREEK  (G4771) su

column7: Hymenaeus, a heretical teacher at Ephesus
column9: From Humen (the god of weddings); "hymeneal"; Hymeneus, an opponent of Christianity -- Hymenaeus.
From  (G5210) humeis; yours, i.e. Pertaining to you -- your (own). see GREEK  (G5210) humeis
Irregular dative case of  (G5210) humeis; to (with or by) you -- ye, you, your(-selves). see GREEK  (G5210) humeis

column8: sing to, sing a hymn of praise unto.
column9: From  (G5215) humnos; to hymn, i.e. Sing a religious ode; by implication, to celebrate (God) in song -- sing a hymn (praise unto). see GREEK  (G5215) humnos

Apparently from a simpler (obsolete) form of hudeo (to celebrate; probably akin to  (G103) aido; compare  (H5667) abowt); a "hymn" or religious ode (one of the Psalms) -- hymn. see GREEK  (G103) aido see HEBREW  (H5667) abowt
Genitive case of  (G5210) humeis; of (from or concerning) you -- ye, you, your (own, -selves). see GREEK  (G5210) humeis

column7: to lead or bring under, to lead on slowly, to depart
column9: From  (G5259) hupo and  (G71) ago; to lead (oneself) under, i.e. Withdraw or retire (as if sinking out of sight), literally or figuratively -- depart, get hence, go (a-)way. see GREEK  (G5259) hupo see GREEK  (G71) ago
From  (G5219) hupakouo; attentive hearkening, i.e. (by implication) compliance or submission -- obedience, (make) obedient, obey(-ing). see GREEK  (G5219) hupakouo

From  (G5259) hupo and  (G191) akouo; to hear under (as a subordinate), i.e. To listen attentively; by implication, to heed or conform to a command or authority -- hearken, be obedient to, obey. see GREEK  (G5259) hupo see GREEK  (G191) akouo

column7: under the power of or subject to a man
column9: From  (G5259) hupo and  (G435) aner; in subjection under a man, i.e. A married woman -- which hath an husband. see GREEK  (G5259) hupo see GREEK  (G435) aner

column7: to go to meet, to meet
column9: From  (G5259) hupo and a derivative of  (G473) anti; to go opposite (meet) under (quietly), i.e. To encounter, fall in with -- (go to) meet. see GREEK  (G5259) hupo see GREEK  (G473) anti
From  (G5221) hupantao; an encounter or concurrence (with  (G1519) eis for infinitive, in order to fall in with) -- meeting. see GREEK  (G5221) hupantao see GREEK  (G1519) eis
From  (G5225) huparcho; existency or proprietorship, i.e. (concretely) property, wealth -- goods, substance. see GREEK  (G5225) huparcho

column7: goods, that which one has, things which one possesseth, substance, that hast
column8: goods, that which one has, things which one possesseth, substance, that hast.
column9: Neuter plural of present participle active of  (G5225) huparcho as noun; things extant or in hand, i.e. Property or possessions -- goods, that which one has, things which (one) possesseth, substance, that hast. see GREEK  (G5225) huparcho

column7: to begin, to be ready or at hand, to be
column9: From  (G5259) hupo and  (G756) archomai; to begin under (quietly), i.e. Come into existence (be present or at hand); expletively, to exist (as copula or subordinate to an adjective, participle, adverb or preposition, or as an auxiliary to a principal (verb) -- after, behave, live. see GREEK  (G5259) hupo see GREEK  (G756) archomai
From  (G5259) hupo and eiko (to yield, be "weak"); to surrender -- submit self. see GREEK  (G5259) hupo
From  (G5259) hupo and  (G1727) enantios; under (covertly) contrary to, i.e. Opposed or (as noun) an opponent -- adversary, against. see GREEK  (G5259) hupo see GREEK  (G1727) enantios

column7: over, beyond, on behalf of, for the sake of, concerning
column9: A primary preposition; "over", i.e. (with the genitive case) of place, above, beyond, across, or causal, for the sake of, instead, regarding; with the accusative case superior to, more than -- (+ exceeding, abundantly) above, in (on) behalf of, beyond, by, + very chiefest, concerning, exceeding (above, -ly), for, + very highly, more (than), of, over, on the part of, for sake of, in stead, than, to(-ward), very. In the comparative, it retains many of the above applications.

column7: to lift or raise over, mid. to uplift oneself
column8: exalt self, be exalted above measure.
column9: Middle voice from  (G5228) huper and  (G142) airo; to raise oneself over, i.e. (figuratively) to become haughty -- exalt self, be exalted above measure. see GREEK  (G5228) huper see GREEK  (G142) airo

From  (G5228) huper and the base of  (G188) akmen; beyond the "acme", i.e. Figuratively (of a daughter) past the bloom (prime) of youth -- + pass the flower of (her) age. see GREEK  (G5228) huper see GREEK  (G188) akmen
From  (G5228) huper and  (G507) ano; above upward, i.e. Greatly higher (in place or rank) -- far above, over. see GREEK  (G5228) huper see GREEK  (G507) ano
From  (G5228) huper and  (G837) auzano; to increase above ordinary degree -- grow exceedingly. see GREEK  (G5228) huper see GREEK  (G837) auzano
